descript.abstract: Street centerline data. Actual and exhaustive street ranges, zip codes and cities for both sides of each street segment. Constructed in conjunction with the parcel basemap. Centerlines are typically at the computed center of the parcel right-of-way lines.
descript.purpose: Q4 2011 - Provide street ranges, zip codes and city names for street addresses

theme.themekt: REQUIRED: Reference to a formally registered thesaurus or a similar authoritative source of theme keywords.

The node id at the beginning of the segment.
The node id at the end of the segment.
Text field that indicates if an emergency vehicle can travel along the segment. A value of "Yes" indicates that a vehicle can travel along the segment and a "No" value indicates that it cannot.
A timestamp date of when the segment was last updated using the RangeEdit tool. RangeEdit automatically updates this field during an edit.
Indicates the type of error in the exhaustive range (see the Maintenance Procedures document).
Contains a comma-delimited list of additional codes if the segment contains more than one error.

Indicates if there is an alternate name that is consistent with MSAG naming standards. Any value greater than "0" indicates an alternate name exists for MSAG purposes. Contains the editor's comment (or "Correction Code") about the type of edit that was made on the segment.
Contains the id of the person who edited the exhaustive ranges of the segment.
Stores additional editor comments up to 250 characters long.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: Street centerline data. Actual and exhaustive street ranges, zip codes and cities for both sides of each street segment. Constructed in conjunction with the parcel basemap. Centerlines are typically at the computed center of the parcel right-of-way lines.
